com.io7m.r1.kernel.types

Class KMesh

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.io7m.r1.kernel.types.KMesh
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.io7m.jcanephora.JCGLResourceSizedType, com.io7m.jcanephora.JCGLResourceUsableType, KMeshReadableType

    @EqualityStructural
public final class KMesh
extends Object
implements KMeshReadableType, com.io7m.jcanephora.JCGLResourceUsableType, com.io7m.jcanephora.JCGLResourceSizedType

    A polygon mesh on the GPU.

    The polygon mesh is expected to have the following type(s):

    • The array buffer must have an attribute of type KMeshAttributes.ATTRIBUTE_POSITION.
    • The array buffer must have per-vertex normals of type KMeshAttributes.ATTRIBUTE_NORMAL.
    • The array buffer must have texture coordinates of type KMeshAttributes.ATTRIBUTE_UV.
    • The array buffer must have per-vertex tangents of type KMeshAttributes.ATTRIBUTE_TANGENT4.
